#. type: multicols
#: sections/trading.tex:20
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\subsection*{Trading Post actions}\n"
"When visiting a \\pagelink{Trading Post}{Trading Post Field}, choose one:\n"
"\\begin{itemize}\n"
"  \\item Trade multiple Resources with the game in accordance with the \\hyperlink{Trade Table}{table at the back cover}.\n"
"  \\begin{expansion}[before skip balanced=0.4em,left=4mm]{rampart,cove}\n"
"    \\item Buy a \\pagelink{War Machines}{War Machine} of your choice.\n"
"  \\end{expansion}\n"
"  \\begin{expansion}[before skip balanced=1em,left=4mm]{stronghold}\n"
"    \\item \\pagetarget{selling Spell Scrolls}{Sell} a \\pagelink{Spell Scroll Cards}{Spell Scroll card} for 2~\\svg{gold} per Spell on it.\n"
"      Remove sold Spells from the game, put the Spell Scroll card into Spell Scroll Deck.\n"
"  \\end{expansion}\n"
"  \\item \\textbf{Remove a single card} from your hand to gain 1 \\svg{gold}.\\par\n"
"    \\note{4}{Specialty, Statistic, Starting Ability and \\wikilink{spells/magic_arrow}{Magic Arrows} \\textbf{cannot be removed} in the Trading Post.}\\par\n"
"\\end{itemize}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/trading.tex:23
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In addition to the above, in \\textbf{Cooperative Scenarios} players can \\textbf{give} resources to other players an unlimited number of times during the same visit.\n"
"\\columnbreak\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/trading.tex:33
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\subsection*{Other Trading actions}\n"
"Certain game modes and game effects also allow you to trade:\n"
"\\begin{itemize}\n"
"  \\item In \\textbf{Alliance Scenarios}, allies may trade Resources freely at any time on their Turns except during Combat.\n"
"  \\item In \\textbf{Alliance and Cooperative Scenarios}, allies may trade \\textbf{Spell} and \\textbf{Artifact} cards in any mix if they have Heroes on adjacent Fields.\n"
"    Only \\textbf{cards from their hands} may be traded and you must give and receive an equal number of cards.\n"
"  \\item When other game effects allow you to \\textbf{trade Resources} (e.g., \\wikilink{events/marketplace}{Marketplace Event}), use the \\hyperlink{Trade Table}{trade table} as well.\n"
"\\end{itemize}\n"
"\\medskip\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

